questions.question: What does the Image(s) to Websocket (Base64) node do in ComfyUI?
questions.answer: The Image(s) to Websocket (Base64) node accepts a batch of image tensors and returns an array of base64 encoded images using the websocket. It also returns a string (Actions) for routing.
questions.subject: Image(s) to Websocket (Base64)

questions.question: How does the Load Image (Base64) node process data?
questions.answer: The Load Image (Base64) node accepts a base64 encoded image and returns an image tensor and mask.
questions.subject: Load Image (Base64)

questions.question: What is the structure of input accepted by the Load Images (Base64) node?
questions.answer: The Load Images (Base64) node accepts a string with the structure: 0x4(Image count) 0x8(Image1 length) Image1(base64) ... 0x8(ImageN length) ImageN(base64).
questions.subject: Load Images (Base64)

questions.question: What does the Load Images (Base64) node return as output?
questions.answer: The Load Images (Base64) node returns a batch of image tensors and masks.
questions.subject: Load Images (Base64)

questions.question: Which node in ComfyUI Knodes can convert image tensors to base64 using websocket?
questions.answer: The Image(s) to Websocket (Base64) node can convert image tensors to base64 using websocket.
questions.subject: Image(s) to Websocket (Base64)

questions.question: What is the function of the Load Image (Base64) node in ComfyUI?
questions.answer: The Load Image (Base64) node in ComfyUI decodes a base64 encoded image and outputs an image tensor and mask.
questions.subject: Load Image (Base64)

questions.question: Which node in ComfyUI Knodes can process a batch of base64 encoded images into image tensors?
questions.answer: The Load Images (Base64) node can process a batch of base64 encoded images into image tensors.
questions.subject: Load Images (Base64)

questions.question: What is the necessary output for routing after processing images with the Image(s) to Websocket (Base64) node?
questions.answer: The Image(s) to Websocket (Base64) node returns a string (Actions) for routing in addition to the base64 encoded images.
questions.subject: Image(s) to Websocket (Base64)
